The paper deals with dimensionality reduction, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories in computer science. The use of subgaussian matrices suggests that the paper may belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses results for sparse and structured sparse vectors, low-rank matrices and tensors, and smooth manifolds, which are topics that fall under the Data Structures (cs.DS), Numerical Analysis (cs.NA), and Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-categories.
